The paper proposes a new sequential data model that efficiently represents state duration and state interval of data events. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves the development of a new model. Additionally, the paper deals with data modeling and analysis, which could also place it in the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses technical requirements and issues, which could suggest that it belongs to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
